.TH hsh 1 "April 2026" "Holberton simple_shell" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple command-line interpreter.
It reads commands from standard input, interprets them, and runs programs.

The shell follows the classic flow:
.RS
read input \-> parse command \-> create child process \-> execute \-> wait
.RE

In interactive mode, it displays a prompt and waits for user input.
In non-interactive mode, it reads commands from piped input or files redirected to standard input.

Error messages are expected to match
.B /bin/sh
format, except that the program name in messages must match
.B argv[0]
of
.BR hsh .
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns 0 on normal exit.
For command execution failures, behavior follows project specifications and shell conventions.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.B PATH
is used to search executable files when commands are not absolute paths.

Other environment variables are inherited from the parent process.
